Former President Olusegun Obasanjo, on Thursday, was conferred with ‘The Order of the Eagle of Zambia’ — first division. Other recipients of the honour, which is Zambia’s highest for civilians, are Ellen Johnson-Sirleaf, former president of Liberia, and Ernest Bai Koroma, former president of Sierra Leone. Hakainde Hichilema, president of the Republic of Zambia, who conducted the investiture ceremony, praised the trio for distinguishing themselves in their countries, in Africa, and globally. Hichilema also praised the recipients “for their unrelenting efforts to establish and promote democracy and good governance, as a precursor to improving livelihoods of their people and other Africans”. See photos below. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-724502" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838879559.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="430" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838879559.jpg 720w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838879559-300x235.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838879559-24x19.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838879559-36x28.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838879559-48x38.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-724500" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838886847.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="367" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838886847.jpg 720w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838886847-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838886847-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/FB_IMG_1657838886847-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpath